UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="course-overview__left" data-coursename="Master of Education (Advanced) " data-coursetype="Postgraduate" data-studenttypes="Domestic, International" id="course-data"> <div class="component rich-text"> <div class="component-content"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">What is a Master of Education (Advanced)?</p> The Master of Education (Advanced) offers current teachers, education practitioners and professionals the opportunity to elevate their knowledge and skills, research capabilities and expertise in targeted areas of educational theory and practice. The course includes a solid foundation in the research of inclusion, leadership, and social justice, providing knowledge and skills to students to be empowered to enact change in program, policy, and project design. Choose from three specialisation streams: <div class="expand-text"> <p><strong>Leadership and Innovation</strong> </p> <p>Through a leadership lens, gain advanced theoretical and practical insights to identify challenges and opportunities in education. Learn to devise effective strategies in response, understand technology''s role in modern learning settings and critically assess contemporary educational innovations. </p> <p><strong>Inclusive Literacies</strong></p> <p> Investigate literacy practices, focusing on diagnosis and intervention. Learn to manage reading literacy in culturally and linguistically diverse contexts. Grounded in research on inclusion, leadership and social justice, the Master of Education (Advanced) equips you to effect change in program, policy and project design. </p> <p><strong>Inclusive Education</strong> </p> <p>Employing a person-centred approach, this course develops skills to address diverse learning needs. Informed by evidence-based research and pedagogy, and neurodivergent community consultations, it equips you to assist autistic and neurodiverse individuals, as well as those with mental health challenges.</p> </div> <p><a class="btn-tertiary jsToggleExpand" data-less="Less" data-more="More" href="#">More</a> </p> </div> </div> <div class="component bullet-list"> <div class="component-content"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Learning outcomes</p> <ul> <li>Apply innovative solutions and evidence-based best practice to complex educational opportunities and challenges.</li> <li>Implement design thinking, research skills and technology initiatives to improve local and global educational practice. </li> <li>Justify and communicate complex educational problems to optimise inclusive teamwork.</li> <li>Model inclusive leadership to impact change in a professional learning context.</li> <li>Demonstrate mastery of the person-centred approach to a diverse range of education contexts.</li> <li>Apply specialised knowledge and skills to design and evaluate inclusive learning environments.</li> <li>Analyse diverse sources of data to inform and assess stakeholders'' learning across diverse educational contexts.</li> </ul> </div> </div> <div class="badges__ctaBtn"> <a class="btn" href="/courses/course-guides/master-of-education-advanced-course-guide" title="Download course guide | Torrens University">Download course guide</a> <a class="btn-link" href="https://apply.torrens.edu.au/" title="Start online application | Torrens University">Start online application</a> </div> </div>',
