UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="course-overview__left" data-coursename="Graduate Certificate of UX Design" data-coursetype="Postgraduate" data-studenttypes="Domestic" id="course-data"> <div class="component rich-text"> <div class="component-content"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">What is a Graduate Certificate of UX Design?</p> The Graduate Certificate of UX Design flips the script on how digital experiences are crafted. You’ll push your skills in user research and dive deep into the core principles of design, all to break the rules of digital customer experiences and create ones that leave a lasting impact. <div class="expand-text"> <p>This course cranks up your current expertise, arming you with modern design practices and methodologies that get results. Through three core subjects, you’ll learn to create bold, design-driven solutions for multi-platform digital spaces. Want to carve your own path? Customise your study with electives in service design, project management, leadership and more.</p> <p>Whether you’re set to dominate the UX world or use this qualification as a springboard into our Master of Design program, you’ll be stepping out with the skills to lead, disrupt and redefine what’s possible in UX design.</p> </div> <p><a class="btn-tertiary jsToggleExpand" data-less="Less" data-more="More" href="#">More</a> </p> </div> </div> <div class="component bullet-list"> <div class="component-content"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Learning outcomes</p> <ul> <li>Analyse and apply current practices and trends in UX design as they relate to social, cultural, economic, technological and environmental contexts.</li> <li>Research complex problems, information, user experiences and theoretical concepts to develop UX design outcomes and solutions.</li> <li>Communicate concepts and processes to justify UX design outcomes or solutions.</li> <li>Demonstrate informed judgement and collaborative skills to participate across global teams and communities.</li> <li>Demonstrate ethical, responsible UX design practices that safeguard individuals, enterprises and societies.</li> </ul> </div> </div> <div class="component badges"> <div class="component-content"><div class="badges__item"> <div class="badges__img"> </div> <div class="badges__text"> <p style="font-weight: bold;"> Free Adobe Creative Cloud Pro licence </p> <p> You''ll receive a free Adobe Creative Cloud Pro licence for the entire time you''re studying Design with us and for six months post graduation. </p> </div> </div> <div class="badges__item"> <div class="badges__img"> </div> <div class="badges__text"> <p style="font-weight: bold;"> DIA-recognised courses </p> <p> </p><p>Certain courses are recognised by the Design Institute of Australia, giving you confidence that your education is of appropriate standing to meet industry expectations.</p> <p></p> </div> </div> <div class="badges__item"> <div class="badges__img"> </div> <div class="badges__text"> <p style="font-weight: bold;"> Complimentary ACS membership </p> <p> Students studying UX and Web Design courses at Billy Blue are eligible for a complimentary ACS student membership. ACS is the largest professional association for Australia''s tech sector with members from across business, government and education. </p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="badges__ctaBtn"> <a class="btn" href="/courses/course-guides/graduate-certificate-of-ux-design-course-guide" title="Download course guide | Torrens University">Download course guide</a> <a class="btn-link" href="https://apply.torrens.edu.au/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Start online application | Torrens University">Start online application</a> </div> </div>',
