UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="course-overview__left" data-coursename="Diploma of Beauty and Spa Practice" data-coursetype="Undergraduate" data-studenttypes="Domestic, International" id="course-data"> <div class="component rich-text"> <div class="component-content"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">What is a Diploma of Beauty and Spa Practice?</p> <p>The Diploma of Beauty and Spa Practice delivers the foundational knowledge and skills you need to apply a range of beauty therapy treatments and techniques. Graduate with the expertise to use the most up-to-date technologies and innovations in your professional practice to help clients look and feel their best.</p> <div class="expand-text"> <p>The Diploma of Beauty and Spa Practice gives you a thorough understanding of beauty and spa technologies, treatments and practices and lets you gain hands-on experience in our student-run clinic, The Practice Wellbeing Centre, under the supervision of practising aestheticians. A collaborative learning environment encourages engagement, allowing you to confidently begin working in the beauty industry as soon as you finish your beauty therapy diploma.</p> </div> <p><a class="btn-tertiary jsToggleExpand" data-less="Less" data-more="More" href="#">More</a> </p> </div> </div> <div class="component bullet-list"> <div class="component-content"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Learning outcomes and Work-Integrated Learning</p> <ul> <li>Apply professional ethics and salon practice in relation to the Beauty/Spa industry </li> <li>Provide a range of beauty/Spa treatments to an accepted professional industry standard </li> <li>Develop interpersonal skills required to work effectively in a team to maintain an inclusive approach to the workplace </li> <li>Develop comprehensive treatment plan to meet client''s needs and expectations </li> <li>Apply solution-based thinking to a range of treatments using discretion and professionalism </li> <li>Interpret policies and procedures that govern the effective, safe and ethical treatments in a Beauty/Spa environment </li> <li>Integrate theoretical knowledge of anatomy and physiology to perform a range of practical treatments </li> <li>Investigate industry trends to enhance professional practice in the beauty/spa industry</li> <li>This course has a requirement of 205 hours of professional clinical practice.</li> </ul> </div> </div> <div class="badges__ctaBtn"> <a class="btn" href="/courses/course-guides/diploma-of-beauty-and-spa-practice-course-guide" title="Download course guide | Torrens University">Download course guide</a> <a class="btn-link" href="https://apply.torrens.edu.au/" title="Start online application| Torrens University">Start online application</a> </div> </div>',
