UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="course-overview__left" data-coursename="Master of Design" data-coursetype="Postgraduate" data-studenttypes="Domestic, International" id="course-data"> <div class="component rich-text"> <div class="component-content"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">What is a Master of Design?</p> The Master of Design prepares you to break boundaries and push design to new heights. This course is for the bold, the rule-breakers and the innovators ready to create human-centred solutions. With a selection of electives, you can tailor your journey to your career ambitions. <div class="expand-text"> <p>Throughout, you’ll sharpen your leadership skills, dive into the world of enterprise and explore how creativity, innovation and entrepreneurship can rewrite economies. In the core subjects, you’ll design artefacts, systems and services that challenge the status quo. Then, dig deeper into cutting-edge areas like user-centred design, sustainability, design leadership, and how design can spark social and economic change. Study face-to-face or online, and if you’ve already got a design background, you can fast-track your way to the finish line. The capstone studio project is your chance to take everything you’ve learned and turn it into a bold, career-defining masterpiece. Ready to disrupt the world of design? This is your launchpad.</p> </div> <p><a class="btn-tertiary jsToggleExpand" data-less="Less" data-more="More" href="#">More</a> </p> </div> </div> <div class="component bullet-list"> <div class="component-content"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Learning outcomes</p> <ul> <li>Critically analyse current practices and trends in design as they relate to social, cultural, economic, technological and environmental contexts.</li> <li>Research complex problems, information and theoretical concepts to inform the development of design outcomes and solutions through independent analysis and synthesis.</li> <li>Communicate advanced concepts and processes to justify design outcomes or solutions.</li> <li>Exemplify informed judgement and effective management to facilitate collaboration across diverse global teams and communities.</li> <li>Practice critical and advanced creative thinking to define and solve problems through complex design projects.</li> <li>Demonstrate ethical, responsible design leadership and practices that safeguard individuals, enterprises and societies.</li> </ul> </div> </div> <div class="component badges"> <div class="component-content"><div class="badges__item"> <div class="badges__img"> </div> <div class="badges__text"> <p style="font-weight: bold;"> Free Adobe Creative Cloud Pro licence </p> <p> You''ll receive a free Adobe Creative Cloud Pro licence for the entire time you''re studying Design with us and for six months post graduation. </p> </div> </div> <div class="badges__item"> <div class="badges__img"> </div> <div class="badges__text"> <p style="font-weight: bold;"> DIA-recognised courses </p> <p> </p><p>Certain courses are recognised by the Design Institute of Australia, giving you confidence that your education is of appropriate standing to meet industry expectations.</p> <p></p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="badges__ctaBtn"> <a class="btn" href="/courses/course-guides/master-of-design-course-guide" title="Download course guide | Torrens University">Download course guide</a> <a class="btn-link" href="https://apply.torrens.edu.au/" title="Start online application | Torrens University">Start online application</a> </div> </div>',
