UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="course-overview__left" data-coursename="Bachelor of Health Science (Naturopathy)" data-coursetype="Undergraduate" data-studenttypes="Domestic, International" id="course-data"> <div class="component rich-text"> <div class="component-content"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">What is a Bachelor of Health Science (Naturopathy)? </p> The Bachelor of Health Science (Naturopathy) teaches a system of healthcare that is based on traditional philosophies and principles and uses a wide variety of tools and techniques to achieve optimal health for a patient. <div class="expand-text"> <p>In this Naturopathy degree, you will learn how to understand the body and disease processes, holistically assess functional disturbances and apply herbal, nutritional and lifestyle medicines and traditional naturopathic techniques to stimulate healing. You will become a client-centred practitioner using evidence-based practice to inform clinical-decision making ensuring an individualised, safe and effective practice approach. </p> <p>The program has a comprehensive compulsory in-person attendance work-integrated learning program that allows students to develop practical skills in herbal manufacturing, and all aspects of clinical practice to heal using natural remedies. You will gain hands-on experience at our custom-built student-led clinic, The Practice Wellbeing Centre, where student practitioners consult with members of the public under the guidance of experienced naturopaths. This will prepare you to confidently start practising and be a qualified naturopath in the community.</p> </div> <p><a class="btn-tertiary jsToggleExpand" data-less="Less" data-more="More" href="#">More</a> </p> </div> </div> <div class="component bullet-list"> <div class="component-content"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Learning outcomes and Work-Integrated Learning</p> <ul> <li>Work within a collaborative health environment to achieve best client/patient care.</li> <li>Explore an array of traditional healing methods from across human history.</li> <li>Consider the role of naturopathy within a community context.</li> <li>Consult with the public under the guidance of experienced naturopaths.</li> <li>This course has a requirement of 460 hours of work-integrated learning.</li> </ul> </div> </div> <div class="component badges"> <div class="component-content"><div class="badges__item"> <div class="badges__img">  </div> <div class="badges__text"> <p style="font-weight: bold;"> ATMS membership </p> <p> Upon graduation, you are eligible to register with the Australian traditional Medicine Society. </p> </div> </div> <div class="badges__item"> <div class="badges__img"> </div> <div class="badges__text"> <p style="font-weight: bold;"> ANTA recognised credentials </p> <p> On graduation, you are eligible to register with the Australian Natural Therapists Association (ANTA). </p> </div> </div> <div class="badges__item"> <div class="badges__img"> </div> <div class="badges__text"> <p style="font-weight: bold;"> WNF peak body membership </p> <p> We are a proud member of the World Naturopathic Federation (WNF), the global peak body for naturopaths. </p> </div> </div> <div class="badges__item"> <div class="badges__img">  </div> <div class="badges__text"> <p style="font-weight: bold;"> CMA recognised qualification </p> <p> Upon completion, you’re eligible to attain membership with the Complementary Medicine Association (CMA). </p> </div> </div> <div class="badges__item"> <div class="badges__img"> </div> <div class="badges__text"> <p style="font-weight: bold;"> NHAA membership </p> <p> Upon graduation, you are eligible to gain membership with the Naturopaths and Herbalists Association of Australia. </p> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="badges__ctaBtn"> <a class="btn" href="/courses/course-guides/bachelor-of-health-science-naturopathy-course-guide" title="Download course guide | Torrens University Australia">Download course guide</a> <a class="btn-link" href="https://apply.torrens.edu.au/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Start online application</a> </div> </div>',
